In Adobe After Effects, you can automate the creation of a rectangle background for a specific part of a text layer using scripting. Since you've specified that the word to be highlighted will be between triple asterisks like `***test***`, you can use a script to find the position of the text to be highlighted and create a shape layer with a rectangle that matches its size.

Here's an example of how you might achieve this using an After Effects script (JavaScript). Keep in mind that you'll need to know the basics of scripting and how to run scripts within After Effects. Also, please note that After Effects scripting doesn't provide direct ways to get the exact size of a substring within a text layer, but we can estimate it:

```javascript
(function() {
    // First we'll get the composition and text layer.
    var comp = app.project.activeItem;
    if (!comp || !(comp instanceof CompItem)) return;
    var textLayer = comp.selectedLayers[0];
    if (!textLayer || !(textLayer instanceof TextLayer)) return;

    // Start the undo group
    app.beginUndoGroup("Create Highlight");

    // Assuming that the text to highlight is wrapped in triple asterisks.
    var textDocument = textLayer.property("Source Text").value;
    var textString = textDocument.text;
    var highlightTerm = textString.match(/\*\*\*(.*?)\*\*\*/);

    if (highlightTerm) {
        // Find the start and end character indices of the term to highlight.
        var startIdx = textString.indexOf(highlightTerm[0]);
        var endIdx = startIdx + highlightTerm[1].length;

        // Create a rectangle shape layer for the highlight.
        var shapeLayer = comp.layers.addShape();
        shapeLayer.name = "Highlight";

        // Add a rectangle to the shape layer.
        var rectangle = shapeLayer.property("Contents").addProperty("ADBE Vector Shape - Rect");
        var rectanglePath = rectangle.property("ADBE Vector Shape");

        // Modify rectangle size and position here as needed
        // You might need to adjust the position and scale based on your specific needs
        // and the font size, font style, and other properties of your text.
        var textScale = textLayer.property("Scale").value;
        var textPosition = textLayer.property("Position").value;

        // Here we're just estimating the size of the rectangle based on the number of characters
        // You may need to refine this logic to take into account font metrics.
        var highlightWidth = highlightTerm[1].length * (textDocument.fontSize * 0.6);
        var highlightHeight = textDocument.fontSize;

        rectanglePath.size.setValue([highlightWidth, highlightHeight]);

        // Positioning the rectangle behind the term to highlight.
        // Since this is a rough approximation, you'll need to adjust the X position and possibly the Y position.
        var preHighlightLength = startIdx - 3; // accounts for the asterisks
        var xOffset = preHighlightLength * (textDocument.fontSize * 0.6);
        shapeLayer.property("Position").setValue([textPosition[0] - xOffset, textPosition[1]]);

        // Set the fill color of the rectangle
        var fill = shapeLayer.property("Contents").addProperty("ADBE Vector Graphic - Fill");
        fill.property("Color").setValue([1, 1, 0, 1]); // Yellow, you can choose any other color here.
    } else {
        alert("No text wrapped in triple asterisks found.");
    }

    // End the undo group
    app.endUndoGroup();
})();
```

